|-angular-cli.json--------------> Used for running  angular cli commands
|-karma.conf.js-----------------> Testing purpose for running tests
|-package.json------------------> Core of npm, specifies what packages are |							installed
|-protractor.conf.js------------> For e2e testing
|-tsconfig.json-----------------> It contains compiler options
|-tslint.json-------------------> Specifies rules for typescript code



1. tslint.json
==================================
a. TSLint is a static code analysis tool used in software development for checking Typescript code quality ,its checkes  if TypeScript source code complies with coding rules

b. It checks the readability,maintainability and functionality errors of typescript code 

c. In this project codelyzer rule set is used  for more info check https://github.com/mgechev/codelyzer

d. Codelyzer is a set of tslint rules for static code analysis of Angular TypeScript projects



2. tsconfig.json
=======================================
a.The presence of a tsconfig.json file in a directory indicates that the directory is the root of a TypeScript project. The tsconfig.json file specifies the root files and the compiler options required to compile the project.

b. For more info https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/tsconfig-json.html



3.package.json
======================================
1. When ever node,npm is used , basic files which is created is package.json

2. Used to install third party packages(plugins) through command propmt



3.angular-cli.json
=======================================
a. Used for running  angular cli commands 

b. Consists projects settings, build directory path, root directory path , e2e testing configuration settings et.. 



